subSubSection.paragraph:
The new species differs from the type species 

E. primordialis

Brues, 1933, by having the body mainly reddish brown and metasoma in posterior half pale brown (entirely black in 

E. primordialis

), antenna basally distinctly pale (entirely black in 

E. primordialis

), fore and middle legs yellowish brown (almost black or dark brown in 

E. primordialis

), length of first flagellar segment 3.7 times its maximum width (2.8 times in 

E. primordialis

), recurrent vein (m-cu) of fore wing longer, about 1.5 times longer than second medial abscissa (2-SR+M) (shorter, not longer than second medial abscissa (2-SR+M) in 

E. primordialis

).
